The '''Finance Director''' is an appointed position of the city of [[Bakersfield, California|Bakersfield]], [[California]]. It is one of five position mandated by the City Charter and one of three positions appointed by the [[Bakersfield City Manager|City Manger]]. The duties of the Finance Director are laid out in Article IV, Section 20 of the City Charter. The director is responsible for the city's finances, assets, and collection of taxes.<ref>''Bakersfield City Charter''. Article IV, Section 20.</ref> The director also assists the City Manager in drafting a budget and provides financial reports to the [[Bakersfield City Council|City Council]] and city departments. The director is also the head of the Financial Department. His office is located in [[Bakersfield City Hall|City Hall North]].<ref>[http://www.bakersfieldcity.us/administration/financialservices/index.htm Financial Department]. City of Bakersfield. Accessed: 04-06-2011.</ref>
